<title>GERMANY: VW sets aside reserves for GM payment.</title>
<headline>VW sets aside reserves for GM payment.</headline>
<dateline>BONN 1997-01-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Volkswagen AG (VW) said it had set aside reserves to cover the payment of $100 million to General Motors Corp as part of an out-of-court settlement of the Lopez dispute.</p>
<p>VW spokesman Klaus Kocks told Reuters in response to an inquiry that the money had already been set aside.</p>
<p>-- Kevin Liffey, Bonn newsroom, +49-228-26097160</p>
